http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/71-hospitals-to-get-facelift-at-Rs.-80-cr./article13989917.ece

Minister for Health and Medical Education Kamineni Srinivas on Friday announced that steps had been taken to develop infrastructure in 71 government hospitals in the State with an expected outlay of Rs. 80 crore.Inaugurating an elevator and a waiting hall, renovated operation theatres and toilets – all built at a cost of Rs. 65 lakh – in the Government General Hospital here, Mr. Srinivas said the GGH was being given a facelift with an expected outlay of Rs. 2.12 crore. He lauded the corporate firms that had come forward to sponsor the works in the hospital. He said more than 3,000 patients were visiting the GGH per day which was a record of sorts at the State-level.